description:
On June 10, 2020, the government of Benin announced a special fund of 74.12bn CFA francs to help workers and firms. The budget will be allocated as follows:

-63.38bn CFA francs for companies of the formal sector;
-4.98bn CFA francs for artesans and providers of services;
-5.76bn CFA francs for poor and extremely poor citizens as discounts on their electricity and water bills.

On 8th, September 2020, the Ministry of Agriculture detailed the measures taken on 29th, July 2020 concerning the support given to the agricultural sector.  A special 100 billion CFA francs fund will be used as follows: 
-50 billion CFA francs for refinancing banks;
-35 billion CFA francs as collaterals for agricultural entrepreneurs' loans;
-15 billion CFA francs for paying the interests of beneficiaries' loans.
